## Known limitations / Sprint 5 warnings
- Analytics is currently based on current application status, not an append-only status history; rejected/ghosted applications can under-report stages previously reached.
- Dashboard is intentionally simple server-rendered HTML + fetch forms; it is interactive but not a polished SPA.
- MCP stdio supports Content-Length framing and newline JSON fallback and is covered by tests, but still needs validation against an actual MCP client in Sprint 5.
- No live external LLM provider eval was run in this shell; provider paths are tested against fake/local compatible providers.
- `sql.js` whole-file writes remain a concurrency risk for simultaneous web/MCP/CLI write-heavy sessions.

## Next action
Commit Sprint 4 locally, then start Sprint 5. First Sprint 5 slice should add status-change history and update analytics/weekly review to use stages reached and time-in-stage, because Claude identified it as the highest-leverage usability improvement.

